Class SingleShapefileOutputHandler

All Implemented Interfaces:
IStreamVisitor
public class SingleShapefileOutputHandler extends ShapefileBaseClass
Coordinate the output of a single buffer for writing the four shapefile component files. The four files are:
  • .shp - the shapefile itself which contains a single kind of geometry information.
  • .shx - the index file, which contains records pointing to the locations in the .shp file for each geometry.
  • .dbf - the attribute file, which is written by a separate handler
  • .prj - a plaintext projection file that identifies the projection in use within the shapefile. Always WGS84 for our classes.
This is a helper class that will not be used standalone.

The shapefile code is inspired by the old mediate code. ShpHandler

Note does not support output of geometry bags to a shapefile in which case it will throw an IllegalStateException.

Author:
DRAND, Paul Silvey for the original Mediate

    • SingleShapefileOutputHandler

      public SingleShapefileOutputHandler(Schema schema, Style style, ObjectBuffer buffer, File outputDirectory, String shapefilename, PointShapeMapper mapper)
      Ctor
      Parameters:
      schema - the schema, never null.
      style - the optional style, may be null
      buffer - the output buffer, never null or empty
      outputDirectory - the output directory, will be created if it does not exist, never null.
      shapefilename - the name of the shapefile to be created. This name will be modified with the standard suffixes to create the actual output shapefile. never null or empty
      mapper - a mapper to go from the url based icons in the Style to a short value for use with ESRI, must not be null if style is not null.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if couldn't create output directory or any of the required arguments are invalid
